Sentencas: Conductivity measurements indicate that lanthanum nickel ferrite (LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3) is a potential cathode current collector material in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Interaction of (La1-xSrx)1-yMnO3-Zr1-zYzO2-d cathodes and LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 current collecting layers for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: However it is known that lanthanum nickel ferrite reacts with zirconia, commonly employed in SOFCs, to form lanthanum zirconate at typical manufacturing temperatures.
Titulo: Interaction of (La1-xSrx)1-yMnO3-Zr1-zYzO2-d cathodes and LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 current collecting layers for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The reaction product, which has a low electrical conductivity, may therefore compromise the use of lanthanum nickel ferrite as a cathode current collector in SOFCs that employ a lanthanum strontium manganite-zirconia composite cathode, such as the Rolls-Royce Integrated Planar (IP)-SOFC.
Titulo: Interaction of (La1-xSrx)1-yMnO3-Zr1-zYzO2-d cathodes and LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 current collecting layers for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: Thus the interaction of lanthanum nickel ferrite with lanthanum strontium manganite ((La0.85Sr0.15)(0.90)MnO3) and 3 mol% yttria-stabilised zirconia has been investigated by powder X-ray diffraction, electrochemical impedance spectroscopy, electron microscopy and energy dispersive spectroscopy.
Titulo: Interaction of (La1-xSrx)1-yMnO3-Zr1-zYzO2-d cathodes and LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 current collecting layers for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: While no interfacial lanthanum, zirconate product was detected, it was found that interdiffusion of manganese and nickel occurred between the perovskite phases of the cathode and current collector layers.
Titulo: Interaction of (La1-xSrx)1-yMnO3-Zr1-zYzO2-d cathodes and LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 current collecting layers for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: Results of electrochemical impedance spectroscopy suggest that the interaction has a strong detrimental effect on cathode performance in the long-term.
Titulo: Interaction of (La1-xSrx)1-yMnO3-Zr1-zYzO2-d cathodes and LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 current collecting layers for solid oxide fuel cell application
